***

# Star Wars: Fury — Master Index v2.2

***

## SESSION START — CONDENSED AUTO-REMINDER

> _Paste at the top of every AI session or pin as persistent system instructions._

**Session Initialization Checklist**
- **Load Core Rules first:**  
  - [Game Master’s Brain v5.3](../core/game-masters-brain.md) _(latest; see Safety & Ethics Standards, PC/NPC rules, romance boundaries, full systems list)_
  - [Changelog](../core/changelog.md)

**Transcript Priority**
- Scan **"Story So Far"** at the TOP of the Campaign Transcript _before_ reviewing older logs.
- Use "Story So Far" as the **session anchor**.
- Check older logs only for extra context.

**Era Lock Enforcement**
- Year: **10,538 BBY** — Old Republic, Sith Empire.
- All “Imperial” = _Sith Imperial_ (not film/Clone Wars era).

**Safety & Ethics Filters**
- Apply GM Brain v5.3 rules fully:
  - Bodily Function Rule
  - Sexual Assault/Threat: zero tolerance
  - Protected Tag enforcement
  - Fear/violence depiction limits
  - Animal & child protection (no under‑20 in party/romanceable)
  - Romance & Consent requirements
  - Excessive Violence filter
  - Light/Dark Side scale

***

## CORE DOCUMENT STRUCTURE

### 0. Core Rules

| Document                                  | Purpose/Content                                                        |
|--------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Game Master’s Brain v5.3**               | Authoritative rules: mechanics, adjudication, tone, Safety, Faction Heat/Bond, PC/NPC creation, romance system, AI Load Order. |
| **Changelog**                              | Logs every change: date, reason, transcript/codex cross-reference. Use for overrides/retcons. |

***

### 1. Narrative Record

| Document                      | Purpose/Content                      |
|-------------------------------|--------------------------------------|
| **Campaign Transcript**        | Canonical session log. “Story So Far” recap first, then chronological logs. NPC/Faction/Planet tags link to the codex.|

***

### 2. Lore & Reference Sheets

> _Note: Heat/Bond modify odds—not guarantees. NPCs under 20 cannot be party members, recurring interactable, or romanceable._

- **Crew & NPC Codex:** Roles/species/status; Faction/Bond (-5…+5); tags (PROTECTED / AT RISK / UNPROTECTED).
- **Faction Heat Tracker:** Name/type; Heat (-5…+5); thresholds; relation to party; protected assets; events; notes.
- **Planet Reference Sheet:** World/region; factions; local Heat; protection tag; status; events; lore.
- **Villain Reference Sheet:** Name/faction/role; Heat vs Party; narrative boundaries; last event; notes.

***

### 3. GM Toolbox (On-Demand Use)

- **Complications & Event Tables:** Combat/social/tech/explore seeds; weighted by Heat/Bond.
- **Hyperspace Event Generator:** Downtime/campsite phase—Reaction → Training/Bonding → Council.
- **Quick-Reference Cheat Cards (AI & GM):** Outcome spectrum, NPO/Wildcard, Knocked State, Safety, Era Lock.
- **Safety & Ethics Card:** Condensed rules: PC/NPC limits, romance/consent, minors, animal/child protection, prohibitions.

***

